48th Dark Elf Wizard on Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 10:53:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Killed my first Raptor today (at 48)</span><hr size=1> Soloed a raptor???  At 48??? I wonder if my 50 wizzy could take one solo with IC then.  gonna have to head there tonight and check it out! <p><a href=#><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/robe.jpg border=0></a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=branaman>Branaman</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/7/01 2:20:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Killed my first Raptor today (at 48)</span><hr size=1> Hmm, i wouldn't try with IC, one resist and you wasted alot of mana. I just was lucky that all my conflags went through for full dmg. Tried it again at 49 with IC, had to gate out 3 times due to resists. <p>Branaman Starbinder <Hated Ones > <BR>
49th Dark Elf Wizard on Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umukaka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukaka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 12:45:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rend seems better...</span><hr size=1> Considering that Ice Coment and Rend have the same damage/mana ratios and cast times, I would tend to pick Rend over IC for the following reasons:<br>
- Rend has instant recast time (IC is 2.5 or thereabout)<br>
- Mobs tend to have less MR than CR<br>
- If you fizzle or get resisted, you lose less with Rend<br>
<br>
I'm no expert though as I've only had the spells for half a level... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umadleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/31/01 4:15:03 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.packetlost.com/ho/fig/diablo2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rend seems better...</span><hr size=1> My advice is to hit Cobalt Scar when u get your next Pillar spell and start quadkiting. Wyverns are a cakewalk compared to Raptors but once you've mastered Wyverns, Raps will seem awfully easy. The main thing about quadding on the islands is learning the spawns and sharing with the other kiters present. You'll make a hell of alot more XP of quadding wyverns and when you hit 53-54 you can move to quadding the Raps. Start by pulling 4 to the chessboard, once you know routes to kite on the island, you're set. <br>
<br>
And the Raptor didn't gate, it's a common bug where, if you're out of melee range of the mob, it warps back to the spawn. This also wipes aggro in a way. If someone else kills it after it's warped back, they will get the XP but if you let it regen and come anywhere close, it'll be on you faster than a fat kid on a smartie. Rule of thumb for wyverns and raptors, when you know it's about to turn to run, get close. If it's snared it will just be standing still and you can med/harvest for that last nuke if OOM and have nothing to worry about.   <p><center><a href="http://www.packetlost.com"><img src="http://www.packetlost.com/ho/eq/xaxsig.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=203.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=192.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=177.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=177.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=177.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=177.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr al